verses.text: In the first year of Darius the son of Ahasuerus , of the seed of the Medes , which was made king over the realm of the Chaldeans ;\f + \fr 9.1 \ft which: or, in which he\f*

In the first year of his reign I Daniel understood by books the number of the years , whereof the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came to Jeremiah the prophet , that he would accomplish seventy years in the desolations of Jerusalem. \p
¶ And I set my face unto the Lord God , to seek by prayer and supplications , with fasting , and sackcloth , and ashes : \p

And I prayed unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* my God , and made my confession , and said , O Lord , the great and dreadful God , keeping the covenant and mercy to them that love him, and to them that keep his commandments ;
We have sinned , and have committed iniquity , and have done wickedly , and have rebelled , even by departing from thy precepts and from thy judgments :
Neither have we hearkened unto thy servants the prophets , which spake in thy name to our kings , our princes , and our fathers , and to all the people of the land.

O Lord , righteousness \add belongeth\add* unto thee, but unto us confusion of faces , as at this day ; to the men of Judah , and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem , and unto all Israel , \add that are\add* near , and \add that are\add* far off , through all the countries whither thou hast driven them, because of their trespass that they have trespassed against thee.\f + \fr 9.7 \ft belongeth…: or, thou hast\f*
O Lord , to us \add belongeth\add* confusion of face , to our kings , to our princes , and to our fathers , because we have sinned against thee.
To the Lord our God \add belong\add* mercies and forgivenesses , though we have rebelled against him;
Neither have we obeyed the voice of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God , to walk in his laws , which he set before us by his servants the prophets.

Yea, all Israel have transgressed thy law , even by departing , that they might not obey thy voice ; therefore the curse is poured upon us, and the oath that \add is\add* written in the law of Moses the servant of God , because we have sinned against him.

And he hath confirmed his words , which he spake against us, and against our judges that judged us, by bringing upon us a great evil : for under the whole heaven hath not been done as hath been done upon Jerusalem.

As \add it is\add* written in the law of Moses , all this evil is come upon us: yet made we not our prayer before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God , that we might turn from our iniquities , and understand thy truth.\f + \fr 9.13 \ft made…: Heb. intreated we not the face of the, etc\f*

Therefore hath the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* watched upon the evil , and brought it upon us: for the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* our God \add is\add* righteous in all his works which he doeth : for we obeyed not his voice.

And now, O Lord our God , that hast brought thy people forth out of the land of Egypt with a mighty hand , and hast gotten thee renown , as at this day ; we have sinned , we have done wickedly.\f + \fr 9.15 \ft gotten…: Heb. made thee a name\f* \p

¶ O Lord , according to all thy righteousness , I beseech thee, let thine anger and thy fury be turned away from thy city Jerusalem , thy holy mountain : because for our sins , and for the iniquities of our fathers , Jerusalem and thy people \add are become\add* a reproach to all \add that are\add* about us.
Now therefore, O our God , hear the prayer of thy servant , and his supplications , and cause thy face to shine upon thy sanctuary that is desolate , for the Lord’s sake.

O my God , incline thine ear , and hear ; open thine eyes , and behold our desolations , and the city which is called by thy name : for we do not present our supplications before thee for our righteousnesses , but for thy great mercies.\f + \fr 9.18 \ft which…: Heb. whereupon thy name is called\f*\f + \fr 9.18 \ft present: Heb. cause to fall\f*
O Lord , hear ; O Lord , forgive ; O Lord , hearken and do ; defer not , for thine own sake, O my God : for thy city and thy people are called by thy name. \p

¶ And whiles I \add was\add* speaking , and praying , and confessing my sin and the sin of my people Israel , and presenting my supplication before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* my God for the holy mountain of my God ;

Yea, whiles I \add was\add* speaking in prayer , even the man Gabriel , whom I had seen in the vision at the beginning , being caused to fly swiftly , touched me about the time of the evening oblation.\f + \fr 9.21 \ft swiftly: Heb. with weariness, or, flight\f*
And he informed \add me\add*, and talked with me, and said , O Daniel , I am now come forth to give thee skill and understanding.\f + \fr 9.22 \ft to…: Heb. to make thee skilful of\f*

At the beginning of thy supplications the commandment came forth , and I am come to shew \add thee;\add* for thou \add art\add* greatly beloved : therefore understand the matter , and consider the vision.\f + \fr 9.23 \ft commandment: Heb. word\f*\f + \fr 9.23 \ft greatly…: Heb. a man of desires\f*

Seventy weeks are determined upon thy people and upon thy holy city , to finish the transgression , and to make an end of sins , and to make reconciliation for iniquity , and to bring in everlasting righteousness , and to seal up the vision and prophecy , and to anoint the most Holy.\f + \fr 9.24 \ft finish: or, restrain\f*\f + \fr 9.24 \ft make an…: or, seal up\f*\f + \fr 9.24 \ft prophecy: Heb. prophet\f*

Know therefore and understand , \add that\add* from the going forth of the commandment to restore and to build Jerusalem unto the Messiah the Prince \add shall be\add* seven weeks , and threescore and two weeks : the street shall be built again , and the wall , even in troublous times.\f + \fr 9.25 \ft be built…: Heb. return and be built\f*\f + \fr 9.25 \ft wall: or, breach, or, ditch\f*\f + \fr 9.25 \ft troublous: Heb. strait of\f*

And after threescore and two weeks shall Messiah be cut off , but not for himself: and the people of the prince that shall come shall destroy the city and the sanctuary ; and the end thereof \add shall be\add* with a flood , and unto the end of the war desolations are determined.\f + \fr 9.26 \ft but…: or, and shall have nothing\f*\f + \fr 9.26 \ft desolations…: or, it shall be cut off by desolations\f*

And he shall confirm the covenant with many for one week : and in the midst of the week he shall cause the sacrifice and the oblation to cease , and for the overspreading of abominations he shall make \add it\add* desolate , even until the consummation , and that determined shall be poured upon the desolate.\f + \fr 9.27 \ft the covenant: or, a covenant\f*\f + \fr 9.27 \ft for the…: or, with the abominable armies\f*\f + \fr 9.27 \ft the desolate: or, the desolator\f*
